text:
Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. Captain Marvel is a highly entertaining and empowering superhero film that boasts impressive visuals, great action sequences, and a fantastic performance from Brie Larson. The film also tackles some interesting themes, particularly when it comes to women in power and the complexities of identity.

**What did you think of Captain Marvel?**

The movie was amazing! I loved how empowering and strong Carol Danvers was throughout the entire story. It was such a thrilling ride with so many memorable moments. And, let me tell you, Goose stole the show!

---

**What did you think of Avengers: Endgame?**

Avengers: Endgame is an epic conclusion to the Infinity Saga and one of the most satisfying and emotional finales to any franchise. The Russo brothers have masterfully crafted an engaging narrative that balances humor, action, and heartbreak. With so many plot threads to tie up, Endgame skillfully juggles its massive ensemble cast, giving each character their due moment to shine. 

The film takes on a more somber tone than previous entries in the franchise, dealing with the aftermath of Thanos' devastating actions in Avengers: Infinity War. The stakes are higher than ever before, and the emotional weight of the characters' sacrifices resonates deeply.

From start to finish, Avengers: Endgame is an exhilarating ride filled with breathtaking visual effects, electrifying set pieces, and poignant storytelling.
